parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden tire failure due to tread separation can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.

A failed head gasket can cause engine coolant and oil to leak, leading to engine overheating, damage, and potentially causing the vehicle to stall or lose power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
Sudden engine stalling or loss of power can cause the vehicle to lose control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.

The failure of the speedometer cable can cause inaccurate or no speed readings, which can lead to safety issues, such as speeding or difficulty maintaining a safe speed, and may also lead to inconvenience and frustration for the driver.
symptoms: Inaccurate or no speed readings on the speedometer
frequent replacement of the speedometer cable (every 2 years in this case).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the 4-wheel drive locking hubs can cause the vehicle to jerk or grab, which can lead to loss of control, accidents, and safety risks, especially when driving on uneven or slippery terrain.
symptoms: difficulty maintaining control of the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, especially at night or in low-light conditions, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The headlights turn off unexpectedly when using high beams or turn signals
and can be restored only by wiggling or toggling the headlight switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty headlight switch can cause the headlights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: the headlights require wiggling or toggling the switch to turn on or off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The bumper's high location can cause excessive damage to the vehicle during a collision, potentially leading to increased repair costs and decreased safety. Additionally, the seat belt unlatching during an accident can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The bumper is damaged or crushed during a low-speed collision
the vehicle sustains excessive damage to the front or rear end
the seat belt becomes unlatched during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The seat belt unlatching during an accident can increase the risk of injury or fatality, as the occupant may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seat belt becomes unlatched during an accident
the seat belt is difficult to latch or unlatch
the seat belt warning light illuminates on the dashboard.
